1
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,840
I'm going to become an influencer.

2
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:27,640
What is an influencer?
How's it different from a content creator?

3
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:32,040
What are KOLs and KOCs? Mega, macro,
micro, nano, how do you measure them?

4
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:36,760
I know how painful it is
when your parents look down on you

5
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:39,400
and don't believe in you.

6
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,720
Let's fight together.

7
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,600
Don't take a single cent
from this old man again.

8
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:53,480
And don't you ever think
you're the only one

9
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,800
who's suffering because you're my son.

10
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:01,440
Thank you so much. Thank you.

11
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,480
Thank you so much.

12
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:15,800
With this kind of thing,
you can't get rich alone.

13
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,400
-We'll get rich together!
-We'll get rich together!

14
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,960
-Very good.
-Thank you.

15
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,960
What are you trading on right now?

16
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,320
Just my phone.

17
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,840
That's not enough.

18
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,200
You need to invest
in setting up a proper system.

19
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:33,800
You ready?

20
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:38,720
Well, yes. No problem at all.

21
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,400
Good. I'll coach you then.

22
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:44,040
-Thank you so much.
-Sure.

23
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,920
<i>If you're serious, you need</i>
<i>to monitor the market closely.</i>

24
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,480
<i>If you want fast profits and quick wealth,</i>
<i>you have to go all in.</i>

25
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,840
<i>Once you have ten million,</i>

26
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:26,800
<i>I can help you make another ten million.</i>

27
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,800
<i>I've got a group that can move the market.</i>

28
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:31,200
<i>When that day comes, we'll talk again.</i>

29
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,760
-Who is it?
-It's me, dear.

30
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,080
Come in, Mom.

31
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,560
What are you doing?

32
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,560
Setting up my workstation.

33
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:02,200
What kind of job is this?
Why do you need so many screens?

34
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:05,640
A day trader, Mom.
I'm going full-time into trading stocks.

35
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,760
Have you told your dad yet?

36
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,960
When Dad ran his business,
he never told me anything.

37
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:20,320
So I don't think I need to tell him
about mine either.

38
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,240
Pound.

39
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,160
Even if he never talked to you
about his work,

40
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,680
he's still your dad.

41
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:33,120
At least tell him,
or talk to him about it, okay?

42
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,920
I know.

43
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:40,840
What I'm doing now is because
I want Dad to be proud of me.

44
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:48,920
Even though he's never encouraged me
or supported me at all.

45
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:54,520
If one day I get rich,
I'll take care of him the best I can.

46
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,080
He will be proud of me, Mom.

47
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,800
Hey, take it away.

48
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:22,160
You only had two bites, Mom.

49
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,760
I can't eat it. I'm going to throw up.

50
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,960
The doctor said you'll need time to adjust
after your first chemo session.

51
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:33,120
Come on, eat a bit more.

52
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,760
-Geez.
-Up.

53
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:37,480
-Come on, so you'll have strength.
-I'm not eating.

54
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,880
-It's really good.
-I said no.

55
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,320
Don't you understand?

56
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,640
Take it away.

57
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,960
-Pong.
-Yes? You want to eat more?

58
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:59,840
Did you write what I told you
to put up for him? Did you do it?

59
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:02,480
I put it up already. It's very visible.

60
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,520
Really? Go.

61
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,400
<i>I'm going out of town.</i>
<i>Not sure when I'll be back.</i>

62
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,320
<i>Don't worry.</i>

63
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,040
<i>Just spend your time working for me.</i>
<i>Go live your life.</i>

64
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:19,480
<i>When you finish the job,</i>
<i>you'll get my shares for sure.</i>

65
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:22,960
<i>I love you more than you think. From Mom.</i>

66
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,720
"Go live your life"?

67
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,600
-<i>Where are you going?</i>
-<i>The night market in the city center.</i>

68
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:40,120
Okay. But before we go, we need to talk.

69
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,120
Talk about what?

70
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,320
You need to say
everything you want clearly.

71
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,840
Say everything in your head out loud.
What you think, want, and need.

72
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:49,320
No need to talk. Just follow me.

73
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,040
No, we can't.

74
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,160
You'll get upset and yell at me again.

75
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,280
It's all because we don't communicate.

76
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,240
If I do something you don't like,
you get unhappy,

77
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,760
then we argue, and then we break up.

78
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:07,480
I mean, break up
as in stop working together.

79
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,520
I'm totally not okay with that.

80
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,000
So you have to say everything clearly.

81
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,920
Who's the boss here,
and who's the assistant?

82
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:21,480
I'm the assistant who wants
to make my boss happy. Now say it.

83
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:30,760
Alright. We need to understand the users,
identify who they are, what they expect.

84
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,640
Interview the target group,
collect data, run focus groups.

85
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,480
Find pain points, develop solutions,
analyze, design the architecture,

86
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,360
set up servers,
design the database and UI,

87
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,040
-program for Android and IOS--
-Wait.

88
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:43,200
Hold it. Let's just do today's part.

89
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,080
See? That's why
I didn't want to explain it.

90
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,440
But you don't need to repeat it.
I recorded everything.

91
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,880
Good. Let's go now.

92
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,880
Wait, let me take a picture of the food.

93
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:09,880
Eat up, Mom and Dad. It's on me.

94
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,480
-Wow.
-Okay.

95
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,640
My daughter is treating us to a big meal.

96
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,360
Where did you get the money from?

97
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,040
From work, of course.

98
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:20,520
Am I hearing things?
My daughter is working?

99
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:25,160
You heard right. I really work. Easy job.

100
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:29,240
Good pay. Just one hour
and I can make almost 200,000 baht.

101
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:33,440
What? One hour and nearly 200,000?

102
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:37,440
That sounds sketchy.
What kind of job is that?

103
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,120
Influencer.

104
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:44,159
What? Influencer?
What kind of job is that?

105
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:47,920
-Huh?
-It's like…

106
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,040
those product reviews I like to watch.

107
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,880
Oh, you mean those people
selling stuff on their phones?

108
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:56,520
No, that's online sellers.

109
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,640
Influencers are way cooler than that.

110
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,680
Oh? How are they cooler?

111
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,920
Just cooler, Dad.

112
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,400
You just take nice photos,
post them often,

113
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:10,000
and get your followers to like them.
That's how you make money.

114
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:12,480
And how long

115
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,600
can you actually earn
from this kind of job?

116
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,480
Don't underestimate it, Dad.

117
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:20,000
Top influencers in Thailand
make tens of millions a year.

118
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:23,520
But the top ones
don't just post pretty pictures all day.

119
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,920
Will you really be able
to do it like them?

120
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,920
I think you should come back
and work at our factory.

121
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:35,840
We make tens of millions a year for sure,
even hundreds of millions.

122
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:40,640
No, I don't want to go back
to the factory. It's boring.

123
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:44,880
I want to be an influencer.
I'm off to a good start. I'll keep going.

124
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:51,800
If you choose that path,
then make your own money.

125
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,120
I'm cutting off your allowance.

126
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,480
And I'm canceling all your credit cards.

127
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,040
Dad, you're joking, right?

128
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:02,680
You'll find out at the end of the month
whether I'm joking or not.

129
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,280
Did you really think that would scare me?

130
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:11,000
I can make my own money.
More than you ever gave me.

131
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,920
Good! So you're that confident?

132
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:18,000
Then I'll cancel your cards
starting today.

133
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,440
Let's see how you survive.

134
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,640
Why do you think I'm going to fail?

135
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:28,920
Why can't you support me?
Don't you believe I can do it?

136
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:33,520
Being looked down on by outsiders
hurts less than by your own parents.

137
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,960
Franc, dear.

138
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,960
Hey, you!

139
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,320
Franc.

140
00:10:57,320 --> 00:11:01,520
Don't be sad, dear.
Your dad is just worried about you.

141
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:05,520
He's more worried about having
no one left to run his business.

142
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:11,840
I understand you've grown up
and want your own life,

143
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,760
but you have to understand him too.

144
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:17,120
He built everything for the family.

145
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,800
He wants you to carry it on.

146
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,480
I do understand him.

147
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:27,240
But he never understands me.
He never trusts me.

148
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,760
Trust me?

149
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,600
Trust Franc.

150
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,720
Yes, that's it, Mom!

151
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:39,760
Thank you.

152
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,000
Franc.

153
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:44,040
Mom, can you pay first?
I'll transfer the money to you later.

154
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:47,200
Tell Dad he can cancel my credit cards
and cut off my money. Go ahead.

155
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,200
I can take care of myself. See you, Mom.

156
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,800
Franc, wait!

157
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:55,840
Flea markets are usually divided
into two types.

158
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,880
Day markets and night markets.

159
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:01,440
But these days, they're broken down
into many more categories.

160
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:06,360
Oh, there's also Art Box markets.
They're more hip

161
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,640
and trendy, popular among young people.

162
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,040
Huh?

163
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,360
Hey.

164
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:23,960
Hey there.

165
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:28,960
We've got more inside.
Come in. Don't be shy. Come on in.

166
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,880
Do you even sell anything?

167
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,360
-Aren't your prices too high?
-Too high?

168
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,040
I'm selling it at the actual price.

169
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:40,720
Some items' prices go up
because market demand is high.

170
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:44,520
I don't think it's okay for you
to talk like that.

171
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,640
But it's not this expensive in Japan.

172
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,240
Even with the exchange rate.

173
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,400
-I think--
-Hey, kid!

174
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,760
If you're not buying, don't mess around!

175
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,080
Get out!

176
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:55,640
-I'm not messing around, I'm serious.
-Sorry.

177
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,280
-Leave!
-I'm being serious!

178
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,240
-Cent, let's go!
-Get out now!

179
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,000
-Why are you yelling at me?
-Watch your mouth.

180
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,280
-Cent.
-Why did you drag me here?

181
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,280
-Why did you say that just now?
-Hey.

182
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:09,120
Didn't you see? The shop's dead quiet
and overpriced. Who would buy that?

183
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,440
Hey, wait. Where are you going?

184
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,960
Over there.

185
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:18,080
Calm down.

186
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:21,600
Just follow me. I'll lead the way, okay?

187
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,480
Stay calm.

188
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:37,120
Take your time browsing, dear.

189
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:54,040
This is just dead capital.
Do you sell anything? The shop is packed.

190
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,000
Sorry, ma'am. Just a moment.

191
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,840
-Do you actually sell anything?
-Cent, come here.

192
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:02,480
-What now?
-Just a second.

193
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,440
Aren't we here to gather information?

194
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:09,440
Cent, listen. I know you mean well.
You see the shops aren't selling.

195
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,240
But you can't talk like that.

196
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,880
-Why not?
-Cent!

197
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:16,160
Let's do it this way.
If you want to know anything,

198
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,560
just tell me and I'll ask for you.

199
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:31,280
Ma'am, I'm sorry about earlier.

200
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:35,920
My boyfriend is just rude.
He doesn't like spending money on me.

201
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:40,400
I knew it. Smart move he's got there.

202
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:42,200
Yeah.

203
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,960
But it's all cleared up now.
He's ready to spend.

204
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:48,280
Then feel free to pick whatever you like.
Everything here

205
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,040
is authentic and beautiful.

206
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:51,960
Okay.

207
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,680
This one's pretty cute.

208
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:07,080
By the way, how have things been?
Are sales good?

209
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:10,120
Dead quiet. Look, no customers at all.

210
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,840
I haven't sold a single bag today.

211
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,360
Whoa, how are you even managing like this?

212
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:16,800
I'm just getting by.

213
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,560
Have you ever tried selling
on social media?

214
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,000
Like Facebook pages, Instagram,
things like that?

215
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,520
Yeah, I boost ads all the time,
but it doesn't really work.

216
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,560
The ads keep disappearing.

217
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:31,000
Then, have you ever tried

218
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:34,480
selling online, like on shopping apps?

219
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:37,920
No, but I'd like to try. Hey.

220
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,120
I want to try live selling,

221
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,760
but I don't know how to do it.

222
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,360
Aw.

223
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:47,240
Then, if there's an app
that lets you try it for free

224
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:51,160
and teaches you step by step,
would you be interested?

225
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,880
If it's not too hard, I'd like to try.

226
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:56,760
That's great. I'm--

227
00:15:56,840 --> 00:16:00,400
Hey, have you picked a bag yet?

228
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:05,200
Here's the thing, ma'am. Let me be honest.

229
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:09,520
My boyfriend gave me a 1,000 baht budget.
What can I get with that?

230
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,400
-A thousand baht?
-Yes.

231
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,160
I've got plenty to choose from.
Wait a moment. I'll bring some out.

232
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,240
A thousand baht, please. Help her out.

233
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:29,840
Can I scan and pay?

234
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:30,760
Here it is.

235
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,960
Why did you buy so many things, dear?

236
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,840
You've got to invest, Mom!

237
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,160
COST, SHELF LIFE, PRICE, PROFIT

238
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:48,280
Hey, over a hundred baht per piece?
Isn't that a bit expensive?

239
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:52,240
Not at all, Mom.
I'm following the standard formula.

240
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,760
I calculate it from cost,
plus 40% miscellaneous costs,

241
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,760
then another 70% profit.

242
00:16:57,760 --> 00:16:59,120
Isn't that a bit too much?

243
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:02,000
It's not, Mom. If we sell it too cheap,

244
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:05,319
people will think it's low quality.

245
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,119
Look, Mom. I use only high-quality stuff.

246
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,599
I only use imported ingredients.

247
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:13,200
The costs are already high, and rent too.

248
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,240
How much are you paying per month?

249
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,920
There's no rent, Mom.

250
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,200
But I do have to give
25% commission to the mall.

251
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,359
Huh?

252
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:24,640
You have to share your cake sales
with the mall?

253
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,400
You work so hard, charge so much,

254
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:31,520
and in the end,
you barely make any profit.

255
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,400
You're right, Mom.

256
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,760
I've set the profit margin too low, Mom.

257
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:43,720
Huh?

258
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:47,160
I should make it 100%.

259
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,240
COST, SHELF LIFE, PRICE, PROFIT

260
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:56,480
Alright. But the mixer and oven
you already have

261
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,840
still work fine. Why did you buy new ones?

262
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:01,320
They're too small, Mom.

263
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,520
If I'm going to open a dessert shop,

264
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:06,160
I need bigger equipment,

265
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,480
otherwise, I can't keep up.

266
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,720
All of this isn't cheap.

267
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:17,160
They're all second-hand,
but they still cost almost 100,000.

268
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,320
Almost 100,000?

269
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,920
Pound is rich, Mom. He can afford it.

270
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,840
SEVEN TECHNIQUES
TO PROFIT FROM DAY TRADING

271
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,800
<i>But you'll need to get</i>
<i>your IC License first.</i>

272
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,600
<i>Once you pass, I'll introduce you</i>
<i>to my friend's brokerage.</i>

273
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,960
<i>You'll be able to trade</i>
<i>for people close to you.</i>

274
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,080
<i>With this kind of thing,</i>

275
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,000
<i>you can't get rich alone.</i>

276
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,000
<i>We'll get rich together.</i>

277
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:59,920
Oh no! Yes, babe?

278
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,760
I'm on my way. Okay, see you.

279
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,480
Mom, where are my car keys?

280
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,800
Well…

281
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:44,320
Pound!

282
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,600
-Pound!
-Dad!

283
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:50,680
-Dad! Stop!
-Pound! Oh no!

284
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,520
Pound, move!

285
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,160
No! Where are you taking the car?

286
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,840
-Dad, stop!
-Dear, stop!

287
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,240
-Dear, stop! Pound!
-Stop the car!

288
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:59,880
What's wrong with you?

289
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,960
Pound, will you move or not?

290
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,520
No way! Where are you taking the car?

291
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:06,600
-I'm selling it.
-Selling it? You can't! That's my car!

292
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,360
I paid for it,

293
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,960
and it's still under my name.
Why can't I sell it?

294
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,400
But you gave it to me.

295
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,360
I can take back whatever I gave you.

296
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,280
No, I won't accept this!
Get out of the car now!

297
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,560
-What's wrong with you?
-You can't take it.

298
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:18,480
-Don't.
-Get out of the car.

299
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,480
-Pound, enough!
-What are you doing?

300
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,040
-Pound!
-Dad, stop!

301
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,680
No, Dad!

302
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,680
Dad!

303
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,360
Dad, it's my car!

304
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:32,960
Dad, don't take my car!

305
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,320
Damn it! It's my car!

306
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,160
Excuse me. Here is your food.

307
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,800
Thank you.

308
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,360
Not eating, babe?

309
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,040
When you said
you'd take me somewhere casual,

310
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,560
I didn't think it would be this casual.

311
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,160
Come on, just once in a while.
Let's change the vibe a bit.

312
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,720
Fancy food all the time can get boring.

313
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:41,800
Sometimes we need
to be more down to earth.

314
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,000
Look at how I'm dressed.

315
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,600
It doesn't even match the place.

316
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,720
If I knew you'd bring me here,
I wouldn't have come.

317
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:55,280
Babe, wait.

318
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,720
Calm down, okay? Don't get mad.

319
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,320
Sit down first.

320
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:09,120
Listen, we'll finish eating quickly,
then we'll go watch a movie.

321
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:10,840
Okay?

322
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,280
You wanted to watch a movie, right?

323
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:17,320
The chicken is good.

324
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:31,560
<i>There are no secrets in this world.</i>
<i>Next time, don't let me catch you</i>

325
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:33,760
punching in and sneaking out.

326
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:36,720
I'll fire you immediately. Got it?

327
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:40,760
Yes, boss. Thank you.

328
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,960
Go now! Get back to work.

329
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:46,640
And remember,
there are no secrets in this world.

330
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,160
What are you drawing?

331
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:58,680
I'm just doodling.

332
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,320
Hey, our uncle didn't hire you
to sit around drawing.

333
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,320
You need to go around inspecting the work.

334
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:06,280
So if a worker makes a mistake
or has an issue, we can fix it right away.

335
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:08,440
You're not here to draw
and play on your phone.

336
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,360
I'm sorry.

337
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:14,480
Don't let me catch you
on your phone or drawing again.

338
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:15,720
Yes.

339
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,440
<i>Can you teach me</i>
<i>how to draw fashion figures?</i>

340
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:35,800
<i>I watched online tutorials,</i>
<i>but I don't get it.</i>

341
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:39,520
Okay, here's the plan.
I'm working with Cent right now,

342
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,960
but after this,
I'll move to the fresh market.

343
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:45,480
Then in the evening,
I'll go to the night market

344
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:46,760
in Thonburi.

345
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:51,760
Can you meet me there? Around 8 p.m.

346
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,760
I'll be done by then, and I'll teach you.

347
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,600
<i>Deal. Thanks a lot.</i>

348
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:59,120
Alright, see you then.

349
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,760
Cent.

350
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:17,000
Do you want to go to the restroom?

351
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:25,080
The bathroom here is really clean.
I just went. It's great.

352
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:30,120
You've been here since morning,
and I haven't seen you go yet.

353
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,560
You're acting like my mom now.

354
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:36,760
Don't accidentally bow to me later.

355
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:48,600
Cent!

356
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,800
Most fresh markets
usually open during the day.

357
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:05,560
These days, there are
more and more fresh markets,

358
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,600
almost in every area.
They're even divided into zones.

359
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,240
I think that's actually good,
because when we go to the market,

360
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:13,000
-we can--
-Hey, watch out!

361
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:18,960
Thank you.

362
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,240
Where to next?

363
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,360
Over on this side, there are shops

364
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:28,280
like IT stores and hair salons.

365
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,360
It's separated from the fresh market zone.

366
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:32,440
-Over there…
-Come with us. Now!

367
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,440
Quiet. Be quiet.

368
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,800
Can I have a few more days?

369
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,000
I really don't have it right now.

370
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,560
It's been days already.

371
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:47,840
I'll pay as soon as I have it.
I really don't have it right now.

372
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,160
Don't have it or just refusing to pay?

373
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,360
Come here! Let me see.

374
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,840
Stop! Don't take it.

375
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:54,840
Stay still!

376
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:58,360
She just needs one or two more days.
Can't you give her that?

377
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:01,960
Do you want me to send this video
to the police, showing you harassing her?

378
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,560
Please?

379
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:11,720
Thank you, dear. Thank you too, young man.

380
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:17,400
-We're here. This is my shop.
-Yes.

381
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:21,800
Alright.

382
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:27,160
Come in. Just put it here.

383
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:38,520
Is business not doing well, Auntie?

384
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,920
Let's not say not doing well.

385
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:42,720
Let's say it's not selling at all.

386
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:45,800
See? Look at this.
I still have so much left.

387
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:49,440
On average, how much do you sell in a day?

388
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:51,920
In the past, I could make
around 1,000 a day,

389
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,880
but these days,

390
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:56,600
I'm lucky if I make 100 or 200 baht.

391
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:59,120
Where will you get money
to repay your debt in two days?

392
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:02,160
I honestly don't know.

393
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,880
I'll buy 3,000 baht worth
of your chili paste.

394
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:09,040
Any kind is fine.
Just pack it all together.

395
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:10,320
CHILI PASTE WITH CRISPY PORK CRACKLINGS

396
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,040
Wow, seriously?

397
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:13,000
I don't like repeating myself.

398
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:16,280
Okay, I'll pack it for you. Just a moment.

399
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:25,600
30 BAHT PER JAR

400
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:29,720
Auntie, I'll take seven jars
of chili paste.

401
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,440
-Seven jars?
-Yes.

402
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:33,840
Sure, dear. One moment.

403
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:47,040
-Auntie.
-Yes?

404
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:48,840
I don't have any coins.

405
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:51,520
Can you give me a ten-baht discount?

406
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:54,200
It's okay, dear. I'll give you a free one.

407
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:56,480
-Thank you.
-No problem.

408
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:00,560
Next time you're going to bargain,
give me a heads up.

409
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,920
Embarrassed?

410
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:10,240
You should try being as broke as me.
You'll stop being embarrassed.

411
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:11,800
Auntie, I'll help you.

412
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,400
Sure, come on.

413
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:15,000
Come here.

414
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:16,080
Here you go.

415
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:17,600
-Like this?
-Yes, wrap it like this.

416
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:20,400
Wrap it nicely.
Pretty people wrap things nicely.

417
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:24,000
-Got it.
-Dear, can you pass me that paper?

418
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:26,520
-Oh, sure.
-Thank you.

419
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:29,920
Yes, that's it.

420
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:33,920
<i>Hello, Franc. Are you ready</i>
<i>to take on new work yet?</i>

421
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:38,480
Work? You've got more clients for me?

422
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:43,120
Yes. A beauty brand
wants you to review lipsticks.

423
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:46,720
The issue is, your image
looks a bit too sad right now.

424
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:50,880
If you're interested, we need to refresh
your image to look more cheerful.

425
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:56,440
I'm interested! I'm really interested.
I want to work a lot, Elle.

426
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:58,240
Peace would've been proud of me for sure.

427
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:02,200
<i>Then it's settled.</i>
<i>I'll handle it with the client.</i>

428
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:07,160
<i>I'll also negotiate the price for you.</i>
<i>You've moved from micro to macro.</i>

429
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:11,680
<i>And later, if you become a KOL or KOC,</i>
<i>you'll earn even more.</i>

430
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:15,000
I'll take care of that part.
I'll email you the details.

431
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:18,040
Yes, Elle. Thank you so much.

432
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:20,400
If there are any more jobs,
contact me anytime.

433
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:21,800
I want to work a lot.

434
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:27,080
Peace would be proud,
and I can finally move on.

435
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,560
Thank you so much.

436
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,480
<i>Thank you too.</i>

437
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:31,800
Yes, goodbye.

438
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,360
Yes!

439
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:45,680
<i>What is an influencer?</i>
<i>How's it different from a content creator?</i>

440
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:49,880
<i>What are KOLs and KOCs? Mega, macro,</i>
<i>micro, nano, how do you measure them?</i>

441
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,680
What are they?

442
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:54,760
KOL stands for Key Opinion Leader.

443
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:58,520
Someone who is trusted, knowledgeable,
and experienced in a specific field.

444
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:01,840
As for KOC, it's basically everyday users

445
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:06,200
who actively use products so much
that people trust their reviews.

446
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:14,880
What about mega, macro, micro, nano?
What are those?

447
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:17,000
That's follower and subscriber counts.

448
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:23,840
What did Elle mean when she said
I'm moving from micro to macro?

449
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:25,240
Huh? Micro to what?

450
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:27,520
Micro to macro.

451
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,720
That's tens of thousands
to hundreds of thousands.

452
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:33,040
Mega is millions, nano is thousands.

453
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,800
Ugh, did you really need to ask that?

454
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,640
Why do you know so much?

455
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:40,240
Shouldn't you already know this?

456
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:43,280
You were the one who told Dad
you wanted to do this job.

457
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:47,280
So he asked me what it is
and how you make money.

458
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,720
Honestly, you should know this before him.

459
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:52,520
Are you insulting me?

460
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:55,720
-I'm not insulting you, I'm just asking.
-That was an insult.

461
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:59,040
Don't think that taking pretty photos,
posting on Instagram,

462
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:01,800
and deleting your ugly
little sister's pictures

463
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:03,440
is enough to become an influencer.

464
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,240
That's not it.

465
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:10,160
What's wrong with you? Got issues?
Come on. We can retake it.

466
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,120
-No.
-Come on. Let's take it.

467
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:14,040
No. You eat it.

468
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:44,120
-Hello, Madam Franc.
-What are you doing after work tonight?

469
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:47,360
I'm meeting Fuang. She's going to teach me
how to draw fashion figures.

470
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:51,360
Hey, perfect. I actually
need to talk to both of you.

471
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:53,480
Where are you meeting her, and what time?

472
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:57,560
Tonight? I can't. I've got work to finish.

473
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:03,040
Yeah, we'll meet another time.
Alright, okay.

474
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:05,160
Hey.

475
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:06,960
Did you forget something?

476
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,800
Hey, of course not.

477
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:13,120
Sorry, babe. I didn't forget.

478
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,680
Thanks for today.

479
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:20,800
It's fine. When will your car be fixed?

480
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:26,040
Probably still a while.
If it's not done next week,

481
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,480
I'll just buy a new one.

482
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,440
See you.

483
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,400
Yes, Mr. Pisit?

484
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,520
Oh.

485
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:08,640
Yes.

486
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,800
Yes, I've heard that.

487
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:16,480
But if it's this big,
I need to consult my dad first.

488
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:22,040
Yes, I'm listening.

489
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:25,680
Honestly, if it's this serious,
I think we should set up a meeting.

490
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:30,560
I'll schedule a time to talk with my dad
and have you join us as well.

491
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:36,600
Yes, alright. Sure.

492
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:08,120
I'm kinda busy right now.
I'm testing a new recipe.

493
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,360
You guys have fun.

494
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:14,040
Hey, Yuan. Can you talk to Fuang

495
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:15,880
about the shop logo for me? Remind her.

496
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:17,520
I'm meeting the sign shop tomorrow.

497
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,560
<i>Okay, that's it then.</i>

498
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:20,600
Thank you.

499
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:41,000
We're going to collect data
from about 20 more shops.

500
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:42,199
Twenty shops?

501
00:34:45,679 --> 00:34:49,520
Okay. Then let's start now.

502
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,199
Let's begin with this one.

503
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:53,360
-Wait.
-Yes?

504
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:56,440
What's wrong?
You look like you're in a hurry.

505
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,720
It's just…

506
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,120
Just what?

507
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:07,720
I'm meeting Yuan at 8 p.m.
to teach him how to draw.

508
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:09,600
Yuan?

509
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,240
The one who wants
to start a clothing brand?

510
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:16,280
Yes. After getting advice from you,

511
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:18,480
he signed up for an online course.

512
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:20,160
He started with drawing,

513
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:24,440
but he said he's still not good at it,
so he asked me to teach him more.

514
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:30,440
Where are you meeting him?

515
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:39,360
Fuang, hi.

516
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:43,000
Hello, Cent.

517
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:46,760
Go ahead and study.
I have some work to do as well.

518
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,000
Yes.

519
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:57,400
Is anyone sitting here? Thank you.

520
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:00,000
I'll sit with you.

521
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,400
I asked him for two hours to teach you.

522
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:07,200
Then I have to get back to work.
Let's start, so we don't waste time.

523
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,520
Okay.

524
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:11,960
Can you try drawing
a standard eight-head fashion figure?

525
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,480
Sure.

526
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,120
-Alright.
-Wait.

527
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:21,920
First thing you should know,

528
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:24,720
tools are very important.

529
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:28,120
A mechanical pencil makes it harder
to draw properly.

530
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:29,320
Also,

531
00:36:30,240 --> 00:36:32,640
this paper isn't very good either.

532
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:34,760
Let's use mine instead.

533
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,800
-Okay.
-Here, a sketchbook.

534
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:40,160
And a wooden pencil.

535
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,680
-A pencil?
-Yeah.

536
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:44,040
-Okay.
-You can have them. I have plenty.

537
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,320
Thanks.

538
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,200
Alright.

539
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:13,960
I know what your problem is.

540
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,520
What's my problem?

541
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:20,840
Your hands are too stiff.
You need to warm them up first.

542
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:23,400
-Warm them up?
-Yeah.

543
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:24,320
Like this?

544
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:27,680
No, not like that. I'll teach you.

545
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,760
But you have to practice every day.
It's your homework.

546
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,200
Okay.

547
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:33,800
-How do I do it?
-I'll show you.

548
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:35,760
Okay.

549
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:39,240
Draw oval shapes.

550
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,640
-Oval shapes
-Like this.

551
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:45,000
Keep drawing a lot of them.
Fill the whole page

552
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:46,480
with ovals.

553
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:51,560
Then practice drawing skirt-like strokes

554
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:54,120
in a connected pattern like this.

555
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:58,640
Back and forth. Got it?

556
00:37:58,720 --> 00:37:59,600
Got it.

557
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,760
It'll make your hands more relaxed.

558
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:04,160
Then draw circles

559
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:08,640
in a spiral like this.
But you have to control the pressure,

560
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:11,080
light and heavy.

561
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:12,760
Keep repeating it.

562
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:18,120
Also, one more basic thing
that's very important, straight lines.

563
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:20,720
You can't just draw stiff straight lines.

564
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,920
You need to control the pressure,
light and heavy as well.

565
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,920
Like this, light and heavy.

566
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,600
Light and heavy.

567
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:31,160
Got it?

568
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:35,480
You have to practice
straight lines, horizontal lines,

569
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:38,360
diagonal lines, curved lines,
and zigzag lines.

570
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:41,960
Practice every day.
I repeat, every single day.

571
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:45,800
Okay, I will. By the way,

572
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:48,440
how does practicing
with circles and stuff actually help?

573
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,600
It builds your hand muscles.

574
00:38:50,680 --> 00:38:53,440
Right now, your hand muscles
aren't really active.

575
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:55,840
That's why your drawing
doesn't come out the way you want.

576
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:59,280
But if you repeat it every day,
it'll get better.

577
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:00,320
Try it and you'll see.

578
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,360
Okay, I'll give it a try.

579
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:10,920
Oh, one more thing. When you draw
straight lines, use your wrist,

580
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,600
but when you draw curved lines,
use your shoulder.

581
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:15,600
It'll make it smoother.

582
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:18,120
-Use my shoulder?
-Yeah.

583
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,880
Like how?

584
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,120
No, not like that. Let me show you.

585
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:25,280
Okay.

586
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,720
Try holding my shoulder.

587
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:32,040
Not the left, right side.

588
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,840
-Here!
-Okay.

589
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:35,600
Watch carefully.

590
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:39,520
Hold it. I'm using my shoulder to draw,
so you can feel the movement.

591
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:40,800
-Watch.
-Okay.

592
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,880
Can you feel it?

593
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,320
-Tell me.
-Yeah, I feel it.

594
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:45,240
Alright.

595
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:48,600
Now I'll use my wrist to draw.
You won't feel much movement.

596
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:49,720
Hold on tight.

597
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:50,880
I'm holding it.

598
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,480
-Here.
-Whoa.

599
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:54,360
Yeah, this time, it's steadier.

600
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:55,600
See?

601
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:58,280
Look at the lines. They're different.
This is wrist drawing,

602
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:00,920
and this is shoulder drawing.

603
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,880
This circle is way better than this one.

604
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:06,440
Let me try drawing too.
Can you check it for me?

605
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:07,920
-Okay.
-Alright.

606
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:11,240
Hold my shoulder and check

607
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,200
if I'm using my shoulder.

608
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,120
-Yes.
-Okay.

609
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,200
-Use your shoulder.
-Got it.

610
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,000
Yes!

611
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,600
Yeah, that's it. Good job!

612
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:23,080
-Let me do another one.
-Okay.

613
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:25,120
-Make it bigger this time.
-Bigger.

614
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:30,080
That's it.

615
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,680
-This is right, isn't it?
-Yes, correct.

616
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:34,720
I've got a good teacher.

617
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:36,840
My talented student!

618
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:40,040
-Come on. Let's keep drawing.
-Okay.

619
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:44,000
Yes, that's it.

620
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:46,560
Yeah, correct.

621
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,960
I think I've got potential.

622
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,440
-Try drawing slowly.
-Okay.

623
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,680
See?

624
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:15,600
Fuang, I feel like my hands
are much more flexible now.

625
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:18,360
Good.

626
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,800
Yong is calling. I'll be right back.

627
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,680
Hey, just talk here.

628
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:30,360
No, I didn't tell him
I came to learn drawing with you.

629
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:34,040
If he finds out, I'm in trouble.
I'll take this somewhere quiet.

630
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:35,280
-Okay.
-I'll be right back.

631
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:43,760
Do you like each other?

632
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,320
Are you asking me?

633
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Cent.

634
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:58,280
You're quite nosy too.

635
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,440
Do you?

636
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:06,720
No. I don't like him,
and he doesn't like me either.

637
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:14,400
How do you know?

638
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:17,920
Because I know who he actually likes.

639
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:21,000
You're pretty nosy.

640
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,480
Hey, are you insulting me?

641
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:27,440
Well, just a little.

642
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,280
Okay, it's done.

643
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,040
I'm going to the restroom.

644
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:53,360
Yes.

645
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,560
-Hey.
-Huh?

646
00:43:03,640 --> 00:43:05,800
Were you two flirting just now?

647
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:11,760
Wow. Guys are so nosy too.

648
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:14,080
Come on, tell me.

649
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,920
No! Just draw.

650
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:20,920
We're out of time. Just practice.
I need to go back to work.

651
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:22,480
Tell me first! What is it?

652
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:24,560
Draw! Just draw!

653
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:27,800
-Focus and draw.
-Okay.

654
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:28,840
Whoa.

655
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,080
-Hey, nice.
-Pretty good, right?

656
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:37,880
Hey, I think that's enough for today.

657
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:41,040
I think I get it now.
You can get back to work for him.

658
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:44,200
Okay, but you still need to practice more.

659
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:46,160
Yeah, I will. I'll practice hard.

660
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:49,400
-I'm off.
-Yeah.

661
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:53,000
Good luck, okay?

662
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:54,160
-Thank you.
-Guys!

663
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,000
-Franc.
-I've got an update.

664
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:58,040
-Sit down. Sit first.
-Huh?

665
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:01,560
Here's the update.

666
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:04,040
Elle called me this morning.

667
00:44:04,120 --> 00:44:06,800
She said there's a new product
that wants to hire me.

668
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:08,040
-Franc--
-Then I thought,

669
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:10,040
I should do something more.

670
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:11,840
So I decided to start a YouTube channel.

671
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:13,960
You're going to be a YouTuber?

672
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:15,920
-Correct.
-Seriously?

673
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:19,160
Seriously! I already have a name for it.

674
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:22,120
-Franc--
-Trust Franc channel.

675
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:23,120
-Franc.
-That's a good name.

676
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:25,720
Hey, you should get up. Come here.

677
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:27,400
-What's wrong? No!
-Come sit over here.

678
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:29,240
-I'm sitting here.
-Seriously, just move.

679
00:44:36,320 --> 00:44:37,720
Did you bring your boss here too?

680
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,200
Move your bag off the laptop.

681
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:41,880
Can't you see something's there?

682
00:44:44,120 --> 00:44:45,440
I can see it.

683
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:50,120
It's a light bag. It's fine sitting there.
What's the big deal?

684
00:44:50,720 --> 00:44:52,440
That's exactly why you're so shallow.

685
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:56,440
You want to be an influencer,
but you don't know what an influencer is.

686
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:58,920
-Calm down.
-Seriously.

687
00:44:59,480 --> 00:45:02,360
We're not even close enough
for you to talk to me like that.

688
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,320
Learn some manners.

689
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:06,600
And the person who puts their bag
on someone else's laptop has manners?

690
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:09,120
Hey, just sit in my seat.

691
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:10,360
-Yeah, sit here.
-Alright?

692
00:45:10,440 --> 00:45:12,200
-Calm down.
-No! I'm not sitting!

693
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:15,000
Sit here first.
Calm down and talk to Yuan.

694
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:16,600
-I'll go finish my work.
-Come talk to me.

695
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:17,920
-Sit here.
-Work?

696
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:20,400
It's this late, and you're still not off?

697
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:25,120
Your boss is seriously harsh.

698
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:28,040
Exploitative, selfish, power-tripping.

699
00:45:28,120 --> 00:45:30,360
Hey, Franc, calm down.

700
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:33,080
I work late because I volunteered.

701
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:36,160
I told him I'm okay with it,
no matter how late it gets. Calm down.

702
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:39,440
Fine. But if he had any conscience,

703
00:45:39,520 --> 00:45:40,960
he wouldn't let you do this.

704
00:45:41,560 --> 00:45:44,520
You're a woman with no car.
It's this late. What if something happens?

705
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:46,360
Would your boss
take responsibility for that?

706
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:48,080
Are you done?

707
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:51,000
One day you'll have no friends left.
Don't be surprised.

708
00:45:51,080 --> 00:45:52,800
With a mouth like that,
do you have any friends?

709
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:57,360
Every word you say hurts people.
Do you even realize that?

710
00:45:57,440 --> 00:45:59,720
-Enough already.
-Probably not, with an attitude like this.

711
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:01,640
-How can you be such a terrible boss?
-Come on.

712
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:02,960
That's enough. Stop it.

713
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:04,480
-Let's go. Enough.
-You're selfish.

714
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:06,040
-Franc, stop.
-Fuang, just quit!

715
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:07,520
Franc, stop it!

716
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:09,240
-I'm not--
-That's enough, okay?

717
00:46:18,240 --> 00:46:20,640
-Stop yelling.
-Didn't you hear what he said to me?

718
00:46:20,720 --> 00:46:22,600
-Let go of me!
-Come with me. Stop.

719
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:25,240
-Listen to me first.
-I'm not done yet!

720
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:26,160
Why'd you drag me out?

721
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:27,600
I said listen to me.

722
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:29,040
Stop insulting him.

723
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:32,960
Look at how everyone is staring at you.
What do you think they're thinking?

724
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:35,680
Good thing no one recorded you.

725
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:40,680
Don't forget, you're getting famous.

726
00:46:40,760 --> 00:46:41,880
Think before you act.

727
00:46:42,640 --> 00:46:47,000
Fine! I won't be angry anymore,
but let me be clear.

728
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:49,760
I don't want to see
that rude Cent ever again.

729
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:52,280
Next time you guys meet him,
let me know, so I won't come.

730
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:57,480
-I'm sorry on my friend's behalf.
-No need to apologize.

731
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:03,120
Some of what your friend said
is actually right.

732
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:07,720
What do you mean?

733
00:47:10,960 --> 00:47:13,080
It's really late already.

734
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:15,640
If it gets any later…

735
00:47:16,840 --> 00:47:17,920
I don't think things through.

736
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,680
Sorry.

737
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:30,600
Do you use PromptPay?

738
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,000
Huh?

739
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,200
Yes.

740
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:38,920
Is it linked to your number?

741
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:40,840
Yes.

742
00:47:56,560 --> 00:47:57,600
Ten thousand baht?

743
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:00,720
Keep it with you.
See you at the office tomorrow.

744
00:48:16,480 --> 00:48:17,480
Thank you, Yuan.

745
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:21,920
About what you said earlier,
what video are you making?

746
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:24,360
I'm going to make
a "move on from Peace" video.

747
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:27,280
Like, "No more sadness.
I'm ready to move on."

748
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:28,720
And I think I want to set up

749
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:31,120
a corner in my house as a studio

750
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:34,040
for product reviews or videos.

751
00:48:35,120 --> 00:48:37,160
But what kind of equipment do I need?

752
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:39,240
Easy. I'll check it for you.

753
00:48:39,320 --> 00:48:41,600
Then, tomorrow I'll go to your place

754
00:48:41,680 --> 00:48:43,880
and see which corner works best, okay?

755
00:48:45,560 --> 00:48:47,520
Thanks, Yuan, my dear friend.

756
00:48:48,240 --> 00:48:49,320
Thank you.

757
00:48:54,880 --> 00:48:57,720
Fuang, Bonus asked me
to remind you about the logo.

758
00:48:57,800 --> 00:49:00,720
She said she's going to make
the sign tomorrow. Is it done yet?

759
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:02,840
-Hey.
-Oh no.

760
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:06,000
I need to rush back and design it.
Yuan, can you drop me off at home?

761
00:49:06,600 --> 00:49:07,520
I'm off then. Bye.

762
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:10,080
Yeah, okay.

763
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:12,680
-Hurry up!
-Okay, let's go.

764
00:49:12,760 --> 00:49:13,840
-Hey, wait.
-See you. Bye.

765
00:49:13,920 --> 00:49:14,920
What about me?

766
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:16,400
Wait for me too.

767
00:49:29,520 --> 00:49:30,960
PYBFF GROUP CHAT
FRANC: GOT HOME NOW, THANKS FOR TODAY

768
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:33,120
<i>Got home now. Thanks for today.</i>

769
00:49:36,760 --> 00:49:38,720
OKAY, I'M HEADING HOME NOW

770
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:41,880
NOTED

771
00:49:47,520 --> 00:49:49,640
Hey, Yuan. Let's grab
something to eat. I'm hungry.

772
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:51,040
Sure.

773
00:49:57,760 --> 00:49:58,600
Hey.

774
00:49:59,160 --> 00:50:00,480
-The meatballs and your drink.
-Thank you.

775
00:50:03,840 --> 00:50:05,080
-Here.
-Let's eat together.

776
00:50:11,440 --> 00:50:12,600
-Hey.
-Huh?

777
00:50:14,920 --> 00:50:18,880
You're not mad at Franc
for arguing with Cent, right?

778
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:22,680
It's been kind of tense since last time.

779
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:29,400
Sometimes I'm just exhausted with her.

780
00:50:30,120 --> 00:50:32,000
When we were kids, I could tolerate it,

781
00:50:32,080 --> 00:50:34,800
but now my patience is really low.

782
00:50:35,880 --> 00:50:39,960
Give me one good reason
why I should still put up with her.

783
00:50:43,320 --> 00:50:44,960
-A good thing about Franc?
-Yeah.

784
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:48,760
She's straightforward.

785
00:50:48,840 --> 00:50:51,360
She's hot-tempered but cools down fast.
She says whatever she thinks.

786
00:50:53,240 --> 00:50:54,840
She can be a bit stubborn.

787
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:57,360
But she really cares about her friends.

788
00:50:58,440 --> 00:51:01,920
She worries when you come home late.
She really cares.

789
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:06,280
She's generous
and gives her all for her friends.

790
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:09,720
She's not perfect.

791
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:11,280
But she does have good points.

792
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:14,760
She really does have a lot of good points.

793
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:17,840
Are there enough good points
for you to like her?

794
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:21,360
I…

795
00:51:21,960 --> 00:51:23,080
You what?

796
00:51:23,160 --> 00:51:24,600
What did you just ask?

797
00:51:28,360 --> 00:51:31,720
You like Franc, don't you?

798
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:39,520
Don't you?

799
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:45,760
Whoa, Yuan!

800
00:51:46,920 --> 00:51:49,400
It's already obvious.
Stop hiding it from me.

801
00:51:49,480 --> 00:51:53,280
Just say it. Tell me.
You like her, right? Answer me.

802
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:55,320
Answer me. What is it?

803
00:51:57,120 --> 00:52:00,320
Fine. If you won't talk,
I'll just call her and ask if she knows.

804
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:05,040
Hey, don't!

805
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:07,880
I'll tell you.

806
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:10,320
-Say it.
-I…

807
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:13,400
I do like her.

808
00:52:14,240 --> 00:52:15,360
I've liked her since school.

809
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:19,680
Since when? How? Tell me!

810
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:22,560
-Say it.
-At first, I didn't like her.

811
00:52:23,280 --> 00:52:25,720
But then it…

812
00:52:26,320 --> 00:52:29,600
slowly grew on me.

813
00:52:31,080 --> 00:52:34,880
I didn't want to go beyond friends,
so I kept it like this.

814
00:52:35,600 --> 00:52:38,440
Aw, Yuan.

815
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:40,960
I'm lucky I didn't expect too much.

816
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:43,480
So I didn't get hurt that badly.

817
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:47,200
Aw, Yuan!

818
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:53,120
But honestly,

819
00:52:53,760 --> 00:52:55,800
Franc doesn't have anyone right now.

820
00:52:57,200 --> 00:52:59,520
And there aren't many people in the world

821
00:52:59,600 --> 00:53:02,720
who can handle her. One of them is you.

822
00:53:05,800 --> 00:53:08,520
I want her to have someone good
looking after her.

823
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:10,120
I think you can do it.

824
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:14,560
I want to be that person.

825
00:53:16,560 --> 00:53:18,920
-But I'm not ready yet.
-Why?

826
00:53:19,440 --> 00:53:23,400
Well, I want to be rich first.
I want stability.

827
00:53:24,240 --> 00:53:27,120
I want to be sure
I can take care of her properly.

828
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:33,120
Then I'll be confident enough

829
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:35,240
to tell her how I feel.

830
00:53:35,320 --> 00:53:38,360
Wow, you're really a gentleman, Yuan.

831
00:53:41,240 --> 00:53:43,000
But honestly,

832
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:46,960
by the time you become rich and ready,
it might already be too late.

833
00:53:48,720 --> 00:53:51,840
I'm saying this
because I've made mistakes before.

834
00:53:52,680 --> 00:53:56,680
With Peace, I told myself
I'd wait until I graduated,

835
00:53:56,760 --> 00:53:59,320
until I was ready,
then I'd take love seriously.

836
00:54:01,080 --> 00:54:02,480
But it ended up being too late.

837
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:11,120
But you're lucky.
You still have a second chance.

838
00:54:11,200 --> 00:54:13,640
Franc is still here for you
to make things right.

839
00:54:15,880 --> 00:54:19,360
Honestly, sometimes being rich
and being in love

840
00:54:19,440 --> 00:54:20,840
might not be connected at all.

841
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:25,520
I don't want you
to make the same mistake I did.

842
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:49,000
<i>I went to order our shop signage.</i>
<i>I also ordered napkins,</i>

843
00:54:49,080 --> 00:54:52,200
<i>cake boxes, and branded bags.</i>

844
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:54,200
<i>Total is about 40,000 baht.</i>

845
00:54:54,280 --> 00:54:56,480
<i>Payment is due today.</i>

846
00:55:09,080 --> 00:55:12,120
<i>Okay, no problem. I'll transfer the money.</i>

847
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:45,760
Where am I supposed to get money from?

848
00:55:48,520 --> 00:55:50,440
Profit sharing? What profit sharing?

849
00:55:50,520 --> 00:55:53,840
You sold my car.
I should get a share of the money.

850
00:55:57,480 --> 00:56:01,320
The car is in my name. I paid for it.
What share are you talking about?

851
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:03,000
Just give me the money instead.

852
00:56:03,600 --> 00:56:05,400
I'll invest it in a business.

853
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:07,920
If you leave money lying around,
it'll disappear day by day.

854
00:56:08,000 --> 00:56:09,320
Start a business?

855
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:13,160
If you want to do it, earn it yourself.
Why are you asking me?

856
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:14,800
I can definitely make money, Dad,

857
00:56:14,880 --> 00:56:18,440
but not today, okay?
I need money to start a business.

858
00:56:18,520 --> 00:56:20,760
As a parent,
you should support your child,

859
00:56:20,840 --> 00:56:22,880
not hold their future back like this.

860
00:56:24,520 --> 00:56:26,440
You only talk about my duties as a father.

861
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:30,200
Have you ever thought
about your duties as a good son?

862
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:33,800
Not just coming to me for money,
wanting this and that.

863
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:38,200
Tell me honestly, have you ever done
anything useful for the family?

864
00:56:38,280 --> 00:56:40,080
I'm doing it, Dad!

865
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:43,920
<i>I will never forget the good times</i>
<i>we had together.</i>

866
00:56:44,600 --> 00:56:47,440
<i>One day, I'll come to you.</i>

867
00:56:50,080 --> 00:56:51,000
I'm not giving it!

868
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:52,600
No! Ouch!

869
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:56,080
This is our last bit of money.

870
00:56:56,160 --> 00:56:58,040
<i>The next day, it might turn into love.</i>

871
00:56:59,160 --> 00:57:01,160
<i>From something neutral,</i>

872
00:57:01,240 --> 00:57:04,040
<i>it may start to feel special.</i>

873
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:06,920
<i>From hopelessness,</i>

874
00:57:07,480 --> 00:57:10,360
<i>it starts turning into hope. From pity</i>

875
00:57:11,640 --> 00:57:13,200
<i>and sympathy,</i>

876
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:17,640
<i>it becomes love.</i>

877
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:04,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
